  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objectives of this trial are to examine the effect of a low FODMAP diet on gut
      microbiota, inflammatory markers, gastrointestinal symptoms and quality of life in patients
      with ulcerative colitis. Furthermore the trial will explore if the response towards a low
      FODMAP diet can be predicted by a patients initial gut microbiota profile. The patients will
      be randomized to an open parallel-group intervention of six weeks duration with intake of
      either a low FODMAP diet or a control diet (habitual diet).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
